President Obama has announced his intent to appoint several individuals to the Council of Governors. The Council, created by Executive Order, will work with defense and national security advisors to exchange views and advice on matters related to the National Guard, homeland defense, and civil support activities. The appointed governors include James H. Douglas of Vermont, Chris Gregoire of Washington, Janice K. Brewer of Arizona, Luis G. Fortuño of Puerto Rico, Brad Henry of Oklahoma, Robert F. McDonnell of Virginia, Jeremiah W. Nixon of Missouri, Martin O’Malley of Maryland, Beverly Eaves Perdue of North Carolina, and M. Michael Rounds of South Dakota. President Obama stated that he is pleased to have governors of exceptional experience join the Council and looks forward to working with them in the future.